# Exercise Part 2: Deepen Understanding Through Guided Questions

### Initial Understanding

Initially, I believed task priorities were simple labels assigned to tasks.

### What I Discovered

Task priorities are implemented using the TaskPriority enumeration:

* LOW
* MEDIUM
* HIGH
* URGENT

These priorities are part of the Task domain model and are used when creating and managing tasks.

### Key Insights

* Priorities are standardized using enums.
* Priority values help organize and filter tasks.
* Business logic uses priority information when managing tasks.

### Misconceptions

Initially I assumed priorities were stored as plain text values. After exploring the code, I discovered they are represented as structured enum values.

